          '<p id="isPasted">Join our family at Pricefx, a <strong>leading SaaS Pricing</strong> (Price Optimization &amp; Management) and <strong>CPQ</strong> (Configure-Price-Quote) vendor. Experiencing consistent annual growth, Pricefx remains committed to <strong>stable employment</strong>. We value flexibility and provide home office and remote work opportunities. Our product boasts <strong>outstanding customer reviews</strong> ranging from small companies to renowned names such as <strong>Michelin, Sonoco, Danone</strong>, <strong>Avery Dennison</strong>, and <strong>Bosch</strong>.</p><p>With branches in 7 countries and over 30 nationalities, Pricefx is a <strong>genuinely international</strong> and <strong>diverse company</strong>, fostering a warm, welcoming, and respectful environment. Join us at Pricefx and be part of a winning team that values your unique contributions, encourages accountability and personal growth, and celebrates collective achievements.</p><h4><strong>Your Mission</strong></h4><p>You will be responsible for executing all HR transactions and administration, supporting the People/HR team, across all HR service categories, including HRIS data maintenance, payroll, reporting, global mobility, and more. This role will provide coverage and support as needed to our employees to ensure their HR-related questions are resolved.   </p><p><br></p><h4><strong>What will be your responsibilities? </strong></h4><ul>\n<li>Serve as an advisor for employees by handling questions and helping resolve work-related problems.</li>\n<li>Analyze and reviews payroll data; ensures compliance with all applicable state and federal wage and hour laws </li>\n<li>Employee benefits management in conjunction with the HR team </li>\n<li>Responsibility for personnel administration and documents related to employment </li>\n<li>Work with immigration attorneys to recommend and secure the proper visa for employees.  </li>\n<li>Compile and complete the necessary documentation to support the visa process </li>\n<li>Screens and refers qualified applicants to the hiring manager for interviewing requirements </li>\n<li>Entry employee medical examinations administration</li>\n<li>Assists with new employee orientation</li>\n</ul><p><strong> </strong></p><h4><strong>What should you have to succeed? </strong></h4><ul>\n<li>Human Resources equivalent experience required </li>\n<li>HRIS experience required, BambooHR experience preferred </li>\n<li>Solid knowledge of Czech labor law  </li>\n<li>Knowledge of German or French labor law would be a big plus</li>\n<li>Good communication skills </li>\n<li>Attention to detail and organizational skills are essential </li>\n<li>Team player and friendly attitude </li>\n<li>Ability to maintain employee confidence and protect operations by keeping HR information confidential. </li>\n<li>Experience in a multinational work environment</li>\n<li>Fluent in Czech and English language</li>\n</ul><h4><strong>Location </strong></h4><ul>\n<li>Prague</li>\n<li>The candidate needs to have a valid work permit for the Czech Republic</li>\n</ul><h4><strong>Other Job Specifics…  </strong></h4><ul>\n<li>Travel required occasionally </li>\n<li>Full-time employment</li>\n</ul><h4><strong>What will you love about us?</strong></h4><p id="isPasted">Our employees appreciate the warm and friendly atmosphere, as well as the flexibility and growth opportunities we provide. Check out our <a href="https://www.glassdoor.com/Overview/Working-at-Pricefx-EI_IE1879589.11,18.htmscore">Glassdoor</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.atmoskop.cz/en/nazory-na-zamestnavatele/2949899-price-f-x-s-r-o">Atmoskop</a> scores and reviews. </p><p>We will support your home office setup with a monthly IT allowance. We prioritize work-life balance and, in addition to vacation, offer work anniversary, birthday, and CSR days off. Building a sense of community is important. We organize regular virtual or in-person meetups and many social activities and challenges.</p><p>We’re proud also to offer some amazing benefits. </p><ul><li>We will allow you to bring your own working equipment by providing an <strong>option of a monthly allowance (3825 CZK Net)</strong> instead of pre-selected working tools (laptop and cell phone)</li><li>We provide<strong> 1750</strong> <strong>CZK in Benefit points</strong>, which can be used for culture, travel, or sports (Multisport card)</li><li><strong>25</strong> days off, <strong>3</strong> sick days, <strong>2</strong> CSR days, and <strong>1</strong> additional day off during your birthday month</li><li>Our offices are exceptional in look and atmosphere, but <strong>you can also work from home or in a park</strong></li><li>A great work-life balance, where you can work full-time on a flexible schedule</li></ul><p><em>B</em><em>y applying, I confirm that I acknowledge and understand how Pricefx processes my personal data as per information in </em><em><a href="https://pricefx.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/UNI/pages/589561897/GDPR+Information+for+Candidates+-+JobScore">GDPR for Candidates</a></em><em>.</em></p>',
